## derived dependency conclusion
Dom constants define three independent public labels: pvac.prf.r.1, pvac.prf.r.2, pvac.prf.r.3.
prf_R(pk,sk,seed) calls prf_R_core three times and multiplies r1*r2*r3; decrypt/encrypt use prf_R_slots, not PRF_R1 alone.
prf_R_core hashes sk.prf_k and mixes the domain into the Toeplitz nonce; therefore public samples bound to pvac.prf.r.1 do not determine pvac.prf.r.2/r.3 without sk.prf_k or equivalent secret-derived material.
verify_lpn_sample_binding.cpp explicitly rejects samples whose domain is not pvac.prf.r.1, confirming the published sample set is one-domain only.
